The PCR primer pairs were as follows: forward, 5′-CCTGAGGTCAGGAGTTCGAG-3′ and reverse, 5′-CCTGAGGTCAGGAGTTCGAG-3′ for Alu-115; forward, 5′-GTGGCTCACGCCTGTAATC-3′ and reverse, 5′-CAGGCTGGAGTGCAGTGG-3′ for Alu-247. Amplification was performed 40 cycles at 95 °C for 30 s, 64 °C for 30 s, and 72 °C for 30 s, following the initial denaturation at 95 °C for 10 min. An arbitrary cutoff value of delta △Rn = 0.65 was used to obtain Ct values. The cfDNA integrity was calculated according to the formula:\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
